race.comment: Pace might be the key to the contest. FIORENOT (6) has relished a couple of fast races and arrives off a pair of wins as a result. Can he adapt if they just hack along now is the question. SUNSETS (5) could be closer third up. Love the way he has found the line in two for the new yard and he can be ready to throw his hat in the ring and win one. Granted it's not something he has done a lot of. TRAPALANDA (11) looked one-paced in Sydney in a slowly-run race so that is a query but he was shaping nicely here prior. TARVUE (10) can get into a great spot and continues to race well. FLAMIN' ROMANS (4) can run a much better race third up from a break. Has won in this spot in the past.
